BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: CONSUMER CREDIT COUNSELING SERVICE OF WESTERN NORTH CAROLINA INC

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: OnTrack WNC helps people achieve their money and housing goals through financial education, counseling and support so that they can overcome crises, afford basic needs, improve money management skills and make sound financial choices rooted in their values.
IRS990.MissionDesc: OnTrack WNC helps people achieve their money and housing goals through financial education, counseling and support so that they can overcome crises, afford basic needs, improve money management skills and make sound financial choices rooted in their values.
IRS990.Desc: The Credit and Money Management program includes face-to-face counseling and group education to assist clients with budgeting, credit, student loans, and debt management plans. Our Financial Capabilities approach moves clients toward their money and housing goals by providing information, action plan development, and supportive accountability. Counselors are certified by the National Foundation for Credit Counseling. This program area also includes the services of the Women's Financial Empowerment Center, the Free Tax Preparation Program, and the SECURE program to build emergency savings funds for low income households.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The Housing programs offer face-to-face counseling and group education to help clients obtain and maintain housing, whether they rent or own or are in the process of buying their first home. Service areas include rental, pre-purchase, reverse mortgages, and foreclosure prevention. This program area includes the employer-assisted matched savings housing programs which are managed with local employers to assist their employees with homebuying. We also manage the NC Foreclosure Prevention Loan Fund for the 18 western counties of North Carolina, providing help for homeowners who are struggling to pay their mortgage due to job loss or other temporary financial hardship. The Organization is a certified HUD Housing Counseling Agency.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: To support the organization's future operating expenses.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: Savings matches for low income households participating in the SECURE program to build emergency savings funds. Amounts are deposited directly into the clients' savings accounts established as part of the program.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Grant funds are paid as savings matches for clients participating in the SECURE program to build emergency savings funds for low income households. Those enrolled participate in ongoing counseling and education activities which monitor their progress towards savings goals.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Before filing, the Form 990 is reviewed in detail by the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors. All Board members are invited to participate in this review session. The Form 990 is reviewed with the full Board at its first meeting following the filing so that Board members may understand the relevance of its content.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: All Directors are required to disclose potential conflicts of interest in writing to the Board as soon as they are aware of the potential conflict. The Board, in the absence of the interested Director, deliberates and votes whether to accept the proposed transaction that gives rise to the conflict. In addition, Directors are required to sign an annual certification that they are not aware of any potential conflicts not previously disclosed.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The salaries of the Executive Director and the Director of Finance are approved by the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors using comparability data and performance indicators. The Committee's deliberation is documented in confidential minutes. This process occurs annually for the salary year beginning July 1.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization makes its governing documents, conflicts of interest policy, and audited financial statements available upon request.

IdRelatedTaxExemptOrgGrp.PrimaryActivitiesTxt: Support of employee assistance programs provided by local employers and donors.
